The Bourne Supremacy by Robert Ludlum
#jasonbourne 

This is the second in series for the book bourne identity, though the book bourne identity did had ended well. This super thrilling second book in line is just as amazing as the first one.

Some two years after learning that he is a trained assassin and breaking his connections with the CIA, Jason Bourne is framed for a crime to cover up the true perpetrator. An attempt on his life by a Russian cop, results in Marie's, the CIA agents death in India. Bourne, thinking that the CIA is hunting him again, proceeds to hunt those responsible for her death and his forgotten past. Bourne discovers that one of the men who oversaw the program which trained Bourne to be an assassin, had stolen millions of dollars from the CIA. Abbott had planned to frame Bourne for the theft, followed by assassinating Bourne in India. Bourne exposes Abbott to another CIA officer in charge of finding Bourne. Abbott kills himself. Bourne goes to Moscow where he is identified, Bourne then goes back into hiding.

Reenter the shadowy world of Jason Bourne, an expert assassin still plagued by the splintered nightmares of his former life. This time the stakes are higher than ever. For someone else has taken on the Bourne identity—a ruthless killer who must be stopped or the world will pay a devastating price. To succeed, the real Jason Bourne must maneuver through the dangerous labyrinth of international espionage—an exotic world filled with CIA plots, turncoat agents, and ever-shifting alliances—all the while hoping to find the truth behind his haunted memories and the answers to his own fragmented past. This time there are two Bournes—and one must die.

